page.title: 05ECOLOGY IN ROSSENDALE
page.content: The commonest{bird}in Rossendale is the the house sparrow.The second commonest is the starling.The five rarest birds are the sparrowhawk,the tawny owl,the coal tit,the kestrel and the treecreeper. The commonest wild {animal}is the rabbit.The rabbit lives in large quantites in the area.The rarest wild is the grey squirrel.There are very few grey squirrels in the area. The{fish }in this area are mostly trout,pike and roach.The commonest fish is the trout. The rarest is the roach. There are very few{reptiles}in this area.The rarest is the grass snake which is harmless.
